{
  "text": " Time flies. Believe it or not, we have just a few weeks left before I take office as the next mayor of New York City. But before then, I would like to quote the great Senator from Vermont. I'm once again asking for your support. I'd like to tell you a little bit more about why we need it. We've had a full plate getting ready for January. We're reviewing the more than 70,000 resumes we've received, setting up our transition committees, naming our appointees we'll turn policy into practice, and planning and budgeting for an inauguration celebration we are so excited to share with you soon. All so we can start delivering on our affordability agenda from day one. Not skipping a beat. We're already at $3.5 million from more than 30,000 donors. And we're so grateful for each and every one of your contributions. But just as a reminder, transitions do not get public matching funds from the city. That means we need just a bit more to help us run through the tape. And I promise two things. The first, none of that money is being used to buy hand warmers like these. And the second is I will stop making these fundraising videos. So head to transition2025.com and go to transition2025.com. And give whatever you can so we can build a city that every New Yorker can afford. Checkmate. So I can once again...",
